---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AreaGuideNav from '../../components/layout/AreaGuideNav.astro';
import CallToAction from '../../components/sections/CallToAction.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Transport & Getting to Chamonix | Chalet Josephine Area Guide"
  description="How to get to Chamonix Mont-Blanc by air, rail, and road. Airport transfers, local transport, and getting around the valley from Chalet Josephine."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: "Area Guide", url: "/area-guide" }, { name: "Transport", url: "/area-guide/transport" }]}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Transport</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-subtitle">Getting to Chamonix and around the valley</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <AreaGuideNav current="/area-guide/transport" />

  <!-- Getting Here -->
  <section class="section-spacing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Getting to Chamonix</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Well connected by air, rail, and road
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="travel-grid">
        <div class="travel-card">
          <h3>By Air</h3>
          <p>
            Geneva Airport (GVA) is the closest major international hub, with direct flights from cities
            across Europe, the UK, and beyond. The transfer from Geneva to Chamonix takes approximately
            90 minutes by road, passing through spectacular scenery along the way. Lyon Saint-Exupéry (LYS)
            is a 2.5-hour drive and offers an alternative with good connections to southern France and beyond.
          </p>
          <ul class="travel-times">
            <li>Geneva (GVA): 90 minutes</li>
            <li>Lyon (LYS): 2.5 hours</li>
            <li>Paris CDG: 5 hours (via domestic connection or drive)</li>
            <li>Turin (TRN): 2.5 hours via Mont Blanc Tunnel</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="travel-card">
          <h3>By Train</h3>
          <p>
            Trains connect Chamonix to Geneva, Paris, and other European cities. The scenic Mont-Blanc
            Express railway runs between Saint-Gervais and Martigny (Switzerland), passing through the
            Chamonix valley with stunning mountain views. From Geneva, the journey combines a mainline
            SNCF service to Saint-Gervais with the Mont-Blanc Express for the final scenic leg.
          </p>
          <ul class="travel-times">
            <li>Geneva: 2.5 hours (train + Mont-Blanc Express)</li>
            <li>Paris: 5.5 hours (TGV to Saint-Gervais + Mont-Blanc Express)</li>
            <li>Zurich: 4 hours (via Martigny)</li>
            <li>Milan: 4.5 hours (via Aosta/Turin connection)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="travel-card">
          <h3>By Car</h3>
          <p>
            Chamonix is well connected by motorway from Geneva, Lyon, and Paris. The A40 (Autoroute
            Blanche) runs directly into the valley. The Mont Blanc Tunnel provides a direct road link
            to Italy and Courmayeur. Chalet Josephine includes private parking for up to 5 vehicles,
            so driving is a convenient option for families and groups.
          </p>
          <ul class="travel-times">
            <li>Geneva: 1 hour 15 minutes</li>
            <li>Lyon: 2.5 hours</li>
            <li>Paris: 6 hours</li>
            <li>Milan (via tunnel): 2 hours</li>
            <li>Courmayeur (via tunnel): 30 minutes</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Airport Transfers -->
  <section class="section-spacing bg-pearl">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Airport Transfers</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Arrive in comfort with a private transfer
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-content">
        <p>
          Our concierge team can arrange private airport transfers directly from Geneva, Lyon, or any
          other airport to the door of Chalet Josephine. Private transfers offer the most comfortable and
          convenient way to start your holiday, particularly for families and groups travelling with
          luggage and ski equipment. Vehicles range from luxury saloons to spacious minibuses for larger
          groups. Transfers can also be arranged for day trips to Courmayeur or Annecy.
        </p>
        <p>
          For those preferring a shared service, regular shuttle buses also operate between Geneva Airport
          and Chamonix, with several daily departures. The journey takes approximately 1 hour 45 minutes
          including stops, and drop-off points are within easy reach of the chalet.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local Transport -->
  <section class="section-spacing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Getting Around the Valley</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Easy, convenient, and often free local transport
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="local-grid">
        <div class="local-card">
          <h3>Free Bus Network</h3>
          <p>
            The Chamonix Bus network connects all the main villages and ski areas in the valley, running
            frequently from early morning to late evening. With the Carte d'Hôte guest card (provided
            with your stay at Chalet Josephine), travel on all local buses is free. The nearest bus stop
            to the chalet is just a short walk away, making it easy to get to any ski area or into town
            without a car.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="local-card">
          <h3>Train (Mont-Blanc Express)</h3>
          <p>
            The Mont-Blanc Express train runs along the valley floor from Les Houches through Chamonix
            to Vallorcine and into Switzerland. It's a scenic and convenient way to access the different
            areas of the valley, and the Carte d'Hôte provides free or discounted travel. The Les Bois
            halt is a short walk from the chalet.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="local-card">
          <h3>On Foot & By Bike</h3>
          <p>
            Chamonix town centre is approximately 15 minutes on foot from Chalet Josephine via a pleasant
            path through Les Bois. The valley is well-suited to cycling, with flat cycle paths running
            along the valley floor. Bikes can be hired locally, and our concierge team can arrange delivery
            to the chalet.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="local-card">
          <h3>Taxis & Private Driver</h3>
          <p>
            Local taxis are available in Chamonix, though they can be busy during peak times. For maximum
            convenience, our concierge team can arrange a private driver and vehicle to be available
            throughout your stay, ensuring door-to-door transport to restaurants, ski areas, and
            excursions whenever you need it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CallToAction
    title="Need Help Planning Your Journey?"
    description="Our concierge team can arrange transfers and transport for your stay at Chalet Josephine."
    primaryButtonText="Check Availability"
    primaryButtonHref="/availability"
    secondaryButtonText="Contact Us"
    secondaryButtonHref="/contact"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-charcoal) 0%, var(--color-alpine) 100%);
    padding: var(--space-20) 0;
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
  }
  .page-hero h1 { color: white; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .page-hero-subtitle { font-size: var(--text-xl); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }
  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .section-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .info-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .info-content p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .info-content p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .travel-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (max-width: 1024px) { .travel-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .travel-card {
    padding: var(--space-8);
    background: var(--color-pearl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  }
  .travel-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .travel-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .travel-times {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .travel-times li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    padding: var(--space-2) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    position: relative;
  }
  .travel-times li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-alpine);
  }

  .local-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .local-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .local-card {
    background: var(--color-pearl);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-8);
  }
  .local-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .local-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .section-header h2 { font-size: var(--text-3xl); }
  }
</style>
